This section contains the full changelog of **Doxee Platform&reg;**** release 6.6**. This release introduced major enhancements to several components of the Doxee Platform&reg;. Please refer to the respective sections for a complete overview of changes.

Before adopting this software version, please read these release notes carefully to find out about new features, improvements, changes, fixes, deprecations, known bugs, limitations, or user impacts which may affect your operations.

- [Workplace 2: New web application, new Human Tasks, new backend](/doxee-platform/docs/release-notes-6-6#workplace-2-new-web-application-new-human-tasks-new-backend)

- [Composer: Major UX and performance improvements on Insertion Points and Building Blocks](/doxee-platform/docs/release-notes-6-6#composer-major-ux-and-performance-improvements-on-insertion-points-and-building-blocks)

- [Update to Apache Tomcat 10](/doxee-platform/docs/release-notes-6-6#update-to-apache-tomcat-10)

## Whatâ€™s new in 6.6
### Workplace 2: New web application, new Human Tasks, new backend
We're excited to introduce Workplace 2, featuring a completely redesigned interface and backend for enhanced usability and responsiveness.

Workplace 2 expands upon the core concept of the original Workplace application but offers an updated experience tailored for B2C communications. Business users can effortlessly switch between managing open workflows and initiating new Business Cases. Supervisors and administrators benefit from the new Business Case Instances view, which provides better monitoring of ongoing workflows.

Alongside the new interface, we've completely rewritten the backend to streamline the creation of Business Cases, making the process quicker and more straightforward. The updated Human Tasks address the most critical use cases from the original Workplace, with more enhancements on the way.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

> Backward compatibility

Workplace 2 represents a complete redesign of the previous Workplace 1 application, including a new technology stack, revamped UX and redesigned Human Tasks. Therefore, a project analysis is necessary before transitioning from Workplace 1 to Workplace 2. We recommend setting up a sandbox environment of Workplace 2 to conduct this analysis. It can run concurrently with the existing Workplace 1 setup.

Workplace 1 will continue to receive maintenance support from now on, limited to critical bug fixes and security patches, and essential updates, without the addition of new features.

### Composer: Major UX and performance improvements on Insertion Points and Building Blocks
Composer received major UX and performance improvements, with particular focus on Insertion Points and Building Blocks. They can now be organized in categories and subcategories. Additionally, they now show labels and tooltips on mouseover, which makes it easier to navigate documents with lots of Insertion Points and multiple Building Blocks. Need to find a particular Building Block quickly? Use the search bar in the Insertion Points tab.

See the full scope of changes in the [Composer release notes](/doxee-platform/docs/release-notes-6-6#composer) below.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

### Update to Apache Tomcat 10
We are pleased to announce that our platform now supports Apache Tomcat 10. This update brings several improvements, including enhanced performance and better scalability for your applications. With support for the latest Servlet specifications, Tomcat 10 ensures improved handling of web requests and more efficient resource management. Additionally, this version includes updated security features to help safeguard your applications.

### Doxee Platform&reg;
> Actions required before installing this version

- Update to **Tomcat 10** before deploying the new Doxee version.

- Migrating databases with the Migrator and Storage Manager tools **requires manual action**. Due to a change in Hibernate, Storage Manager doesn't properly remove generated objects during the clear action, leading to failures during the import action. To prevent errors during the database migration process, it is necessary to manually delete the old sequence before initiating the import action.

- Doxee Platform&reg; **no longer supports Windows Server 2016**. Please check the Software &amp; Hardware Requirements for supported servers.

#### **Server Infrastructure &amp; Runtime**
- **Added **support for Tomcat 10, enabling compatibility with the latest servlet container versions.

> Backward compatibility

Due to incompatibility with previous Apache Tomcat versions, the update to Tomcat 10 is mandatory.

- **Updated** Apache FOP rendering processor to 2.10.

#### **Access Management &amp; Security**
- **Added **new `IRoleManager` configuration, allowing administrators to configure and assign custom user roles for more flexible access control.

> Backward compatibility

The roles `owner`, `potential_owner,` and `watcher_owner` can no longer be assigned globally. Assigning one of these roles globally would lead to authentication errors.

- Assigning the unassignable roles `authenticated`, `unauthenticated`, `owner`, `watcher_owner,` and `potential_owner` now returns an error.

- **Added **validation checks for the `state` and `nonce` parameters in OpenID authentication to enhance protection against replay and CSRF attacks.

- **Updated** IPD version to `5` due to the new optional `priority` flag to enable precise control over authentication resolution.

> Backward compatibility

The default credentials registry priority is `0` for global credentials registries and `1` for process credentials registries; this default value will be silently applied by the system for credentials registries without an explicit `priority` configuration. IPD files migrated from previous versions will assume a credentials registry default of `0` for backward compatibility with existing behavior.

- **Fixed **an issue where credential registry priorities were not correctly resolved, causing entries with different priorities to overwrite each other. This occurred due to default priorities not being propagated through the `InfinicaEngineContext`. The expected behavior is that unmarshalling will now throw an error when encountering duplicate entries.

- **Fixed **incorrect â€œImpersonation not enabledâ€ error messages in the audit log, which previously swapped the original and impersonated usernames when impersonation was attempted while not enabled.

- **Updated** various libraries:

activemq to 5.19.0

- commons-configuration to 2.12.0

- jackrabbit to 2.22.0

- mina-core to 2.2.4

- mochito to 5.17.0

- bytebuddy to 1.17.5

- mysql-connector-j to 9.3

- pdfbox to 2.0.34

- poi-ooxml to 5.4.1

- tika to 2.9.4

- **Fixed **SOAP server projects compiling generated code for wrong Java version.

#### **Stability &amp; Performance**
- **Fixed **caches without timeout values not triggering their associated removal listeners, ensuring consistent cleanup and event handling behavior across cache types.

- **Fixed** process storages exported with Storage Manager containing empty Process Watchers. The missing data would subsequently trigger exceptions when trying to reimport the storage.

- **Fixed **an issue where clearing the execution cache would sometimes close the resources of actively running processes.

- **Fixed **a bug that prevented the right-click context menu from being displayed in some cases.

#### **Editor**
- **Added **support for the Signature element. Users can now sign documents by drawing in the signature form field or uploading their signature as an image.

- **Added **the new Optional Content element. This element can be used to fill leftover page space which would have remained empty after the document is rendered.

- **Added** the property `element-label` extension to all elements. The value of this property can be displayed in the Outline by navigating to the App Settings tab &gt; Editor settings &gt; Element labels and selecting one of the options showing the description.

- **Improved:** The `border-radius` property is now shown in the editor area. This property can be used to round the corners of element borders.

- **Improved **the drop-down menus of suggested valid values for properties to utilize the entire width of the text input field.

- **Changed:** The output and editor view settings were moved into a dedicated App Settings tab in the right panel menu.

- **Fixed** drag &amp; drop indicator not disappearing after the action is completed but remaining in the editor area.

- **Fixed **tooltips not disappearing after mouseover and moving to a random area on the screen.

- **Fixed **a bug that prevented horizontal resizing of the text input field when editing Text elements within the Outline.

- **Fixed **a visual glitch that caused an empty drop-down bar to be displayed under text input fields when editing properties.

- **Fixed **a bug that caused erratic caret behavior in the RGB color picker.

- **Fixed **a bug that caused a reset of page-masters' names to the default string. This occurred after changing the name manually but not confirming the change with the Enter key.

- **Fixed **missing import in dependency analyzer.

#### Style &amp; Properties
- **Added **the new Wrapper element. This element can be used to propagate properties to its children, thereby simplifying property management. This element requires POWER_USER or ADMINISTRATOR rights.

- **Added** the option`shrink-to-fit` to the `overflow` property. It changes the size of dynamically resolved values to fit the fixed size of its enclosing element, for example block or inline containers, table cells or form fields. This setting is especially useful in cases when text values coming from variable data such as addresses might be expected to exceed the size of the provided field.

- **Added **basic support for rotated elements. The rotation can be controlled in discrete steps with the property `reference-orientation`and can only be applied to Container elements.

> Technical limitation

Due to technical limitations, rotation is not shown in the editor but is visible in the preview.

- **Added **missing configuration dialog to the Form Field section in the Style &amp; Properties tab. Form Fields can be configured using options like read-only, required, or password.

- **Added **missing tooltips to the overline and strikethrough text formatting buttons.

- **Added: **Inserting a Refreshable will trigger an input dialog to set a name for the block. This name is saved as the property `template-name`.

- **Improved **the `border` section in the Style &amp; Properties tab to visualize the new radius properties. They can be used to round the corners of element borders.

- **Improved: **The bold text formatting button is now displayed as activated when the `font-weight` property is set to "600" or higher.

- **Improved** the reporting of inherited values in the Style &amp; Properties tab. If a property isn't inheritable, child elements will display the value `auto`. This only applies to elements and properties with direct inheritance rules.

- **Fixed **non-inheritable properties being incorrectly reported as inherited in the Style &amp; Properties tab.

- **Fixed **changed property value also being applied to the next selected element after it was changed on one element. This could potentially lead to loss of content.

- **Fixed **an issue that caused invalid values to be set on table cells after the table row alignment was changed with formatting buttons.

- **Fixed **incorrect validation errors and unexpected behavior when an invalid property value was entered in the Style &amp; Properties tab.

- **Fixed **wrong German tooltip text for the strikethrough text formatting button.

- **Fixed **long XPath expressions overflowing the border of the template page. Long strings are now shortened with `...`.

#### Tables
- **Improved: **Individual table cells can now be deleted by pressing the Delete key.

> Backward compatibility

Deleting individual cells may cause the surrounding cells to shift in unexpected ways.

- **Changed:** Table rows can now be moved into condition branches inside the table body using established drag-and-drop, copy/paste and shortcut operations.

- **Fixed **a bug which compromised the structure of accessibility metadata. This occurred when an element was tagged as a table header.

#### Template Parts

- **Added **an error event in cases where the template couldn't be correctly saved due to Tomcat exceptions.

- **Improved: **Template thumbnails now displays only the visible part of the first page sequence. Previously, the entire template would have been resized to fit the thumbnail tile, potentially resulting in a distorted aspect ratio of the image.

#### Building Blocks

#### External Document

- **Added: **Double-clicking the External Document element in the editor area now opens the filepicker dialog.

- **Improved: **Properties for External Documents are now collected in a dedicated submenu of the Properties tab.

#### Image Handling
- **Added **loading indicators for images to show that an opened document is not fully loaded yet. Page breaks will be recalculated after the document is fully loaded.

- **Added **support for rendering TIFF images in the editor area.

- **Added **support for rendering images with uppercase file extensions in the editor area: jpeg/JPEG, jpg/JPG, png/PNG, tiff/TIFF.

#### Data Management
- **Improved: **Overflowing values of Repeats, Conditions, Toggles, Dynamic Values, Dynamic Blocks, Numbering References and Tables of Content elements will now be shortened with `...` to fit the available screen width. The last part of the value will be displayed.

#### Preview

- **Added **a toggle to activate and deactivate test cases. If toggled, the test case data will be used for generating previews.

- **Changed **XPath validation errors not causing PDF preview to fail. XPath errors in condition branches will now cause the PDF preview to fail. This is consistent with expected behavior when encountering XPath errors in critical places.

- **Fixed **HTML previews being rendered using PDF output configurations.

- **Fixed **broken custom previews Composer Human Task, Composer NG Human Task and Workplace PDF.

- **Fixed **dynamic values used for test cases not being updated for the PDF preview. In particular, if the XML test data was changed in the data preview, the subsequently generated PDF wouldn't reflect the changes until the application was reloaded.

#### Filepicker
- **Added **import of external XSL files that can be used in document templates.

- **Added **the new preview type Intermediate Format, which can be used in the Output Management integration by users with the POWER_USER role. It downloads a zipped folder containing an input XML file, the IF file, and images.

- **Improved: **Files and Folders in the filepicker dialog can now be viewed in the new tile mode. The view can be switched using a new toggle in the upper right-hand corner of the dialog window.

- **Improved: **The thumbnail visualization in filepicker was aligned with the dashboard screen.

- **Added: **The External Document element no longer requires a PDF to be selected. This change accommodates scenarios when the file is resolved dynamically at runtime.

- **Improved **the generation process of template thumbnails to reduce the file size of the generated image. Only the visible segment of the first page-sequence-element will be captured. If the first section of the template contained high-resolution images embedded from the local filesystem, the generated thumbnail file could potentially exceed the allowed file size, leading to errors when trying to save the template.

- **Fixed **an issue which caused the indirect version history to fail for referenced files whose URI contained empty spaces.

- **Fixed **missing namespace definition `pdf:catalog` when generating Intermediate Files.

- **Fixed **failing upload of ITX files from the filepicker dialog.

- **Fixed **loading issues of images in filepicker tiles and improved focus handling when using keyboard navigation.

- **Fixed **missing thumbnails for ITX files in the filepicker (tile mode).

### Process Engine
#### **Usability Enhancements**
- **Added** process messages in end states in the process log.

- **Added** a new task element parameter which allows to block users from completing the task. This parameter can be used to ensure that the creator of a task can't approve their own work, for example.

- **Improved** volatile processes so that theyâ€™re no longer lost after approximately 17 minutes.

- **Changed** the behavior of iteration targets on start elements in included processes, which lead to an accumulation of outputs.

> Backward compatibility

This fix addresses an undesired change in behavior which occurred from version 6.5 onwards. Iteration targets now again behave as expected in version 6.4.

- **Improved** the handling of warnings from deprecated activities. These warnings were moved from the process logs into diagnostic-log and application-log to prevent errors and disruptions.

- **Improved:** Reduced the log level for ProcessTerminateException to avoid redundant termination warnings when a process is terminated purposefully.

- **Fixed** nonexistent sub-pipeline variables, for example in a group, inheriting the types of unmapped homonyms from a parent pipeline. This issue would manifest as seemingly unrelated errors, for example corrupted PDFs.

#### **Integration &amp; Module Extensions**
- **Added** support for JDBC drivers in the extension directory. This enables users to add JDBC drivers to command line tools without having to manually modify the class path.

- **Added** the possibility to create extra module directories through the command line using the new `-a` and `-b` options.

- **Improved **Process Engine REST API query parameter `autoDispose` which now allows camel case spelling for enum values, in addition to the value of the Java enum field.

- **Added** the `getMetadata` API endpoint to retrieve helpful process metadata.

- **Changed** the return element names of getAttributes, `getFeatures`, and `getMetadata` from `jaxMapEntries` to `attributes` to improve clarity.

- **Changed** and updated IPD version to `5` due to the new optional `priority` flag, which allows to define a priority order when querying multiple sets of credentials for a matching server entry.

> Backward compatibility

The default credentials registry priority is `0` for global credentials registries and `1` for process credentials registries; this default value will be silently applied by the system for credentials registries without an explicit `priority` configuration. IPD files migrated from previous versions will assume a credentials registry default of `0` for backward compatibility with existing behavior.

#### **Namespaces &amp; XML Schema**
- **Fixed** wait state result XMLs declaring an unused namespace.

- **Improved** the namespaces of bundler scripts, updating it from `http://www.infinica.com/process_v2` to `http://www.infinica.com/process-engine`.

### Template Designer
#### **UI/UX Enhancements &amp; Usability**
- **Added** the new Optional Content element. This element can be used to fill leftover page space which would have remained empty after the document is rendered.

- **Improved** the handling and validation of Chart formatting. The invalid value `justify`is now allowed for horizontal alignment; itâ€™s mapped to the valid value `center`.

> Backward compatibility

Starting from this version, an exception will be thrown when an invalid chart definition is found. Previously, an empty definition would be substituted for invalid values, which lead to rendering errors.

- **Improved **list prefix and suffix distance values which are now dynamic. This prevents overlapping text in cases when the prefix or suffix has a very long value.

- **Fixed** application startup issues caused by the Jakarta update.

- **Fixed** an issue with adding text elements by opening the right-click context menu and selecting Add new &gt; Text. If the action was done once and then repeated, the second attempt would not register.

- **Fixed** an issue that caused the error `org/apache/pdfbox/io/RandomAccessRead` when adding a PDF as an Image or External Document element to a template.

- **Fixed** a visual bug that caused dynamic values to be cut off in the Designer preview. This issue occurred when its parent block contained static text and a dynamic value and the font size of the block was increased.

- **Fixed** an issue that caused errors when adding indexing dependencies to the Dependency Analyzer.

- **Fixed** broken navigation to an included Template Part Reference (local or external) through the context menu or by double-clicking the reference in the Dependencies view.
